The paper deals with the complexity of counting problems associated with various satisfiability, graph and combinatorial problems, when restricted to planar instances. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational geometry (cs.CG), and/or discrete optimization (cs.LO). Among these, cs.CC and cs.DS seem to be the most likely categories, as the paper deals with the complexity of counting problems and their associated decision problems, which are central topics in computational complexity and data structures. However, the paper also involves graph theory and combinatorics, which are relevant to cs.DM and cs.LO, and planar instances, which are relevant to cs.CG. Therefore, these categories are also likely candidates.
